More than twenty sequences of song forms can resolve into hidden harmonies.
These are not listed here. Bards are expected to discover them through
performance. Archetypes can deepen certain hidden harmonies, adding extra
momentum, lingering resonance, and distinct thematic messages.

When you discover a hidden harmony or cause a song field to pivot into a
deeper pattern, your Bard soul records it. Use bpatterns to review what you
have learned. Use bpatterns harmonies, bpatterns pivots, or bpatterns <name>
to narrow the list and see how to trigger a learned pattern again.

Charisma matters to hidden harmonies. A more charismatic Bard can draw more
momentum out of a resolved pattern and hold the resonance longer.

Active songs also matter to other Bard commands. A Bard with the right field
already moving can make related powers stronger:

   Rhythm       helps timing, followers, combat pressure, and support tempo
   Melody       helps healing, calm, social influence, and control
   Harmony      helps party support, role songs, lore, and precision
   Dissonance   helps fear, morale damage, tricks, and enemy control
   Crescendo    helps burst pressure, Finales, and dramatic command moments

For example, Soothe benefits from Melody or Dissonance, Rally benefits from
Harmony or Rhythm, Wail benefits from Dissonance, Crescendo, and Finale
pressure, and Study benefits from Harmony or precise hidden patterns.

Some songs can also shift enemy morale. At higher guild levels, use study on a
target to read the emotional resonance your music has left behind.

INSTRUMENTS AND ARCHETYPES

Alternate Bard instruments can change how battle songs behave. Buy them at
the Bard Shoppe in the Darkwind Bard guildhall. Use instrument to list carried
instruments, instrument <name> to select one, and instrument off to return to
your base lute. See bardhelp instruments.

At guild level 10, specialize chooses a Bard archetype. Archetypes shape song
momentum, field strength, instrument affinity, field flavor, and hidden harmony
resonance. See bardhelp archetypes.

